==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Loathly
<hw>Loath"ly</hw> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧th"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Unwillingly; reluctantly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This shows that you from nature <qex>loathly</qex> stray.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧⟦th⟧"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr> <def>So as to cause
loathing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With dust and blood his locks were <qex>loathly</qex> dight.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loathness</ent>⟦br⟧
